00:20:15,083 --> 00:20:16,791
Hello, Preecha.

278
00:20:16,875 --> 00:20:18,708
Hello!

279
00:20:21,541 --> 00:20:23,250
Bad reception.

280
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:29,875
Boy!

281
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:33,958
Boy!

282
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:36,708
You.

283
00:20:37,291 --> 00:20:38,708
The lady is calling you.

284
00:20:38,791 --> 00:20:40,625
-Really?
-Really!

285
00:20:41,458 --> 00:20:44,958
Do you know the alley
behind The Grand Postal building?

286
00:20:47,416 --> 00:20:49,208
You are a bikeman.
How come you don't know it?

287
00:20:55,375 --> 00:20:56,916
Now what, Suree?

288
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:00,208
She didn't answer the phone.
Will she be able to get here?

289
00:21:01,708 --> 00:21:03,416
Who are you talking to?

290
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:04,916
No one. I'm just muttering.

291
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,750
You mutter very loudly.

292
00:21:06,833 --> 00:21:08,041
So what?

293
00:21:11,958 --> 00:21:13,833
Go straight.
Turn left at the next traffic light.

294
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:15,708
Go straight.

295
00:21:15,791 --> 00:21:17,708
Turn left at the next traffic light.

296
00:21:20,291 --> 00:21:21,375
But...

297
00:21:21,458 --> 00:21:22,625
You sound very familiar.

298
00:21:31,583 --> 00:21:32,666
Have we met?

299
00:21:40,125 --> 00:21:41,208
Are you from Ayutthaya?

300
00:21:47,083 --> 00:21:48,958
You look familiar, too.

301
00:21:52,833 --> 00:21:54,666
Why don't you answer her question?

302
00:21:57,666 --> 00:21:59,250
What?

303
00:21:59,833 --> 00:22:01,708
I only said he was acting weird.

304
00:22:01,791 --> 00:22:03,083
Why did he take off?

305
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:09,166
-Why did you run a red light?
-So we'll get there quickly.

306
00:22:09,250 --> 00:22:10,541
I'm not in a hurry.

307
00:22:10,625 --> 00:22:11,625
Are you fake monks?

308
00:22:11,708 --> 00:22:12,791
What?

309
00:22:12,875 --> 00:22:14,333
Are you working together?

310
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:16,291
-No, we--
-Where's your alms bowl?

311
00:22:16,375 --> 00:22:17,833
Where's your temple boy?

312
00:22:17,916 --> 00:22:19,541
-We--
-Someone will pick you up, right?

313
00:22:20,791 --> 00:22:24,000
Don't lie to me. I'm an ex-cop.

314
00:22:30,166 --> 00:22:31,291
Shit!

315
00:22:39,208 --> 00:22:41,375
-Accident ahead!
-I know.

316
00:22:42,500 --> 00:22:44,250
Stop the bike!

317
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:47,000
Your eyes give it away.

318
00:22:47,083 --> 00:22:48,833
Keep it cool, man.

319
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,625
Watch out!

320
00:22:58,875 --> 00:23:02,708
Bikers always ride on the sidewalk.
How dangerous!

321
00:23:02,791 --> 00:23:03,791
Luckily,

322
00:23:03,875 --> 00:23:05,833
I helped you just in time.

323
00:23:06,125 --> 00:23:08,500
I wish I could've used my hands,

324
00:23:08,583 --> 00:23:10,375
but my hands are not available. So I--

325
00:23:10,458 --> 00:23:12,166
-Kicked me.
-Yes.

326
00:23:12,250 --> 00:23:13,208
You don't mind, right?

327
00:23:13,291 --> 00:23:14,541
I don't.

328
00:23:15,541 --> 00:23:17,416
Father, watch out!

329
00:23:24,166 --> 00:23:25,791
Thank you very much.

330
00:23:25,875 --> 00:23:27,666
I owe him my life.

331
00:23:27,750 --> 00:23:30,500
I'm glad that you saved him
from a fatal accident.

332
00:23:30,583 --> 00:23:31,666
You don't mind, right?

333
00:23:31,750 --> 00:23:34,333
-I don't.
-He doesn't mind.

334
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:40,166
What are you doing?

335
00:23:47,791 --> 00:23:52,000
Honey, have I told you
that Sak got promoted?

336
00:23:52,583 --> 00:23:54,333
He follows in your footsteps.

337
00:23:54,416 --> 00:23:55,666
Same position.

338
00:23:55,750 --> 00:23:59,083
Are you happy? I am really happy.

339
00:24:04,458 --> 00:24:05,375
Hey, Sak!

340
00:24:05,791 --> 00:24:07,708
You're back already?

341
00:24:08,375 --> 00:24:09,583
Suree,

342
00:24:09,666 --> 00:24:11,416
I took your fridge to the repair shop.

343
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:13,041
-Really?
-It's really broken.

344
00:24:13,125 --> 00:24:14,833
Nothing works.

345
00:24:14,916 --> 00:24:16,375
I want to ask you something.

346
00:24:16,750 --> 00:24:18,291
The story you told me.

347
00:24:18,375 --> 00:24:19,208
Who was he?

348
00:24:19,291 --> 00:24:21,041
If I knew,
would I ask you in the first place?

349
00:24:22,125 --> 00:24:25,500
He sounded and looked familiar.

350
00:24:25,583 --> 00:24:28,458
But I've never known any bikemen.

351
00:24:31,250 --> 00:24:32,166
Well, hear me out.

352
00:24:32,583 --> 00:24:36,208
Next time I go selling dolls in Bangkok,
take me to the spot where you met him.

353
00:24:36,291 --> 00:24:39,125
I will find out who he is.

354
00:24:39,208 --> 00:24:40,500
Trust me,

355
00:24:40,583 --> 00:24:43,041
he won't get away from an ex-cop like me.

356
00:24:48,833 --> 00:24:50,500
Why are you sweating like pig?

357
00:24:52,583 --> 00:24:54,750
-I sweat easily.
-Really?

358
00:24:55,541 --> 00:24:56,916
Let me see.

359
00:24:57,875 --> 00:24:58,708
What are you doing?

360
00:24:58,791 --> 00:25:01,375
Checking your pulse.

361
00:25:04,500 --> 00:25:06,666
Your pulse is dancing like a go-go girl.

362
00:25:15,708 --> 00:25:17,208
-Suree.
-Yeah?

363
00:25:17,291 --> 00:25:18,875
-Do you think he's weird?
-Who?

364
00:25:18,958 --> 00:25:20,958
Your son.

365
00:25:21,041 --> 00:25:22,208
I don't think so.

366
00:25:22,291 --> 00:25:24,333
You are the weirdest one in this house.

367
00:25:24,416 --> 00:25:26,166
I'm not.

368
00:25:26,750 --> 00:25:28,000
Your mom is the weirdest.

369
00:25:28,958 --> 00:25:30,083
Have you changed her battery?

370
00:25:30,458 --> 00:25:31,833
She's still like a statue.

371
00:25:33,416 --> 00:25:35,833
You are really rude. Just go away.

372
00:25:35,916 --> 00:25:38,833
When you have time,
play a fun song so she can dance.

373
00:25:59,375 --> 00:26:01,125
I FIXED YOUR BUTTON

374
00:26:18,333 --> 00:26:19,416
Long!

375
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:21,625
-Long!
-What's up?

376
00:26:21,708 --> 00:26:23,583
What can I do for you?

377
00:26:23,666 --> 00:26:25,208
Can someone deposit this check for me?

378
00:26:28,458 --> 00:26:31,416
The bank will be closed in ten minutes.

379
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:32,416
Yeah, I know.

380
00:26:32,500 --> 00:26:34,625
No problem.

381
00:26:35,583 --> 00:26:37,416
I'll ask Sak to run this errand.

382
00:26:40,458 --> 00:26:41,666
-Sak.
-Yes?

383
00:26:41,750 --> 00:26:44,875
Go to the bank
and deposit this check for our client.

384
00:26:44,958 --> 00:26:47,791
Don't you see
I have to deliver these pork rinds?

385
00:26:49,125 --> 00:26:51,583
I know, but it's the same way.

386
00:26:51,666 --> 00:26:54,083
You can drop by the bank
and deposit the check.

387
00:26:54,166 --> 00:26:55,166
Go! Go! Go!

388
00:26:57,333 --> 00:26:58,833
This moron.

389
00:26:59,750 --> 00:27:01,375
I must tell him everything.

390
00:27:04,541 --> 00:27:06,083
This guy is fast.

391
00:27:20,708 --> 00:27:22,583
You're dead meat!

392
00:27:25,208 --> 00:27:26,833
Naa, ain't you pretty?

393
00:27:26,916 --> 00:27:28,416
Thank you very much.

394
00:27:28,500 --> 00:27:30,000
You are glowing.

395
00:27:30,083 --> 00:27:32,708
Have you been working out or something?

396
00:27:32,791 --> 00:27:34,041
I jog.

397
00:27:34,125 --> 00:27:35,291
You jog.

398
00:27:35,375 --> 00:27:37,458
You have to watch out for accidents.

399
00:27:37,541 --> 00:27:39,750
I have a new interesting insurance plan.

400
00:27:39,833 --> 00:27:43,291
-Yes, I'm looking for one.
-I'll choose the best plan for you.

401
00:27:43,375 --> 00:27:45,083
If you die soon,

402
00:27:45,166 --> 00:27:48,375
your kids won't get much money,
but the funeral will be grand.

403
00:27:48,458 --> 00:27:50,166
But if you live for a long time,

404
00:27:50,250 --> 00:27:52,250
your kids will be very rich.

405
00:27:52,333 --> 00:27:53,875
Are you interested?

406
00:27:59,291 --> 00:28:00,625
Hold on!

407
00:28:00,916 --> 00:28:02,083
The bank is closed.

408
00:28:02,166 --> 00:28:03,375
You can't close now.

409
00:28:03,458 --> 00:28:04,750
We still have three minutes.

410
00:28:04,833 --> 00:28:06,541
Is your watch running slow?

411
00:28:06,625 --> 00:28:09,041
No way! See this?
I still have three minutes.

412
00:28:09,125 --> 00:28:11,083
The time on my watch matches Big Ben.

413
00:28:11,166 --> 00:28:12,166
What is Big Ben?

414
00:28:12,250 --> 00:28:14,958
It's a place we use to set the time.

415
00:28:15,041 --> 00:28:16,833
Next time, explain it that way.

416
00:28:16,916 --> 00:28:18,541
Don't use big words. I don't understand.

417
00:28:18,625 --> 00:28:20,208
I'm tired and confused. You understand?

418
00:28:22,250 --> 00:28:23,875
I bought a new phone.

419
00:28:24,125 --> 00:28:26,958
I'm not boasting.
This one can do FaceTime.

420
00:28:27,041 --> 00:28:29,416
What is FaceTime?

421
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:31,166
You are such a hillbilly.

422
00:28:31,750 --> 00:28:34,500
If you use FaceTime,
you can see their face, too.

423
00:28:34,583 --> 00:28:36,708
Big face on the screen.

424
00:28:37,041 --> 00:28:39,208
-Wait!
-What, bro?

425
00:28:39,291 --> 00:28:41,458
Why all the hurry?

426
00:28:41,541 --> 00:28:43,583
What's the big deal?
I just want to deposit a check.

427
00:28:43,666 --> 00:28:44,791
It's a big deal.

428
00:28:44,875 --> 00:28:46,000
It's a big deal.

429
00:28:46,083 --> 00:28:47,416
My life is like this.

430
00:28:47,500 --> 00:28:49,875
So unfortunate
that I have to meet a dude like you.

431
00:28:49,958 --> 00:28:52,791
Can you give my position some respect?

432
00:28:52,875 --> 00:28:55,583
Give me some respect as a guard!

433
00:28:56,458 --> 00:28:58,166
Thailand is always like this.

434
00:28:58,250 --> 00:29:00,125
If it's ten people, then it's ten checks.

435
00:29:00,208 --> 00:29:01,750
Rules are not respected.

436
00:29:01,833 --> 00:29:03,541
If I could choose,

437
00:29:03,625 --> 00:29:05,291
I'd have fled to Italy.

438
00:29:05,375 --> 00:29:07,458
-I'm annoyed. I'm fed up.
-Just a sec.

439
00:29:07,541 --> 00:29:08,583
What?

440
00:29:12,708 --> 00:29:13,625
What's going on, Mom?

441
00:29:13,708 --> 00:29:15,333
It's FaceTime.

442
00:29:15,416 --> 00:29:17,083
I know what FaceTime is.

443
00:29:17,166 --> 00:29:20,291
I want to see how you're doing at work.
My dear boy.

444
00:29:21,250 --> 00:29:23,750
-See? I'm working.
-Wait. Wait.

445
00:29:23,833 --> 00:29:25,916
Your bank is closed now.
Did you finish your job?

446
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:29,166
It will be closed soon.
Why do you want to know?

447
00:29:30,708 --> 00:29:31,666
Close the door, Wichien.

448
00:29:31,750 --> 00:29:33,916
-I have to go.
-Who is Wichien?

449
00:29:34,625 --> 00:29:37,166
-We don't have time, Wichien.
-Stop! Stop!

450
00:29:37,708 --> 00:29:38,541
What's going on?

451
00:29:39,083 --> 00:29:40,291
I have a check to deposit.

452
00:29:41,083 --> 00:29:44,291
You want to deposit a check?
Let me see.

453
00:29:53,125 --> 00:29:54,041
The bank is now closed.

454
00:29:54,625 --> 00:29:55,875
Can you come back tomorrow?

455
00:30:00,541 --> 00:30:02,458
I told you.

456
00:30:02,958 --> 00:30:04,958
Please leave.

457
00:30:08,166 --> 00:30:11,166
Hello, teacher. The bank is closed.

458
00:30:11,708 --> 00:30:13,750
Can you tell the client that I'm sorry.

459
00:30:14,125 --> 00:30:15,250
Okay.

460
00:30:33,916 --> 00:30:36,375
What are you doing?

461
00:30:36,458 --> 00:30:37,958
Where are you going?

462
00:30:38,041 --> 00:30:40,125
We are going to battle.
Mind your own business.

463
00:30:40,208 --> 00:30:41,125
-Wait.
-What?

464
00:30:41,208 --> 00:30:42,250
What does "battle" mean?

465
00:30:42,333 --> 00:30:44,666
Scum like you--

466
00:31:01,250 --> 00:31:03,000
That motherfucker!

467
00:31:13,500 --> 00:31:16,166
Scumbag, I'm exhausted from chasing you.

468
00:31:17,625 --> 00:31:18,666
I'm fucked.

469
00:31:18,750 --> 00:31:21,208
Let me see your stupid face.

470
00:31:26,750 --> 00:31:27,583
You wanna fight me?

471
00:31:28,791 --> 00:31:29,958
Damn it!

472
00:31:30,041 --> 00:31:31,291
My old wound. Fuck!

473
00:31:45,375 --> 00:31:46,541
Shit!

474
00:31:48,583 --> 00:31:49,583
Shit!

475
00:32:04,875 --> 00:32:07,666
I'm leaving. My dad is here.

476
00:32:07,750 --> 00:32:10,000
I have to get the hell out.

477
00:32:10,416 --> 00:32:11,791
Stop.

478
00:32:11,875 --> 00:32:13,291
I told you to stop.

479
00:32:13,375 --> 00:32:14,791
I told you to stop.

480
00:32:14,875 --> 00:32:16,750
It's you guys, right?

481
00:32:18,416 --> 00:32:19,500
I didn't do anything.

482
00:32:22,833 --> 00:32:25,000
I have petty crimes on a daily basis,

483
00:32:25,083 --> 00:32:27,208
instead of working on big cases.

484
00:32:27,625 --> 00:32:30,000
I have to find the guy
who punched the security guard.

485
00:32:30,083 --> 00:32:32,125
I didn't punch him.
The other guy punched him.

486
00:32:34,125 --> 00:32:37,500
The fine for an assault case is ten grand.

487
00:32:37,583 --> 00:32:38,416
What?

488
00:32:38,500 --> 00:32:40,041
Can I pay 500?

489
00:32:40,125 --> 00:32:42,583
The fine is between 500 and 10,000.

490
00:32:42,666 --> 00:32:44,625
So you won't do it again.

491
00:32:44,708 --> 00:32:47,041
If you don't pay, you can go to prison.

492
00:32:52,125 --> 00:32:54,208
What's wrong?

493
00:32:54,291 --> 00:32:55,625
I lost my wallet.

494
00:33:06,166 --> 00:33:07,625
They always have an excuse.

495
00:33:08,333 --> 00:33:11,708
Then call your family to bail you out.

496
00:33:15,916 --> 00:33:17,041
MY FAVORITE CONTACTS

497
00:33:22,708 --> 00:33:25,333
MOM

498
00:33:26,583 --> 00:33:28,333
-Why can't you call your mother?
-Sir,

499
00:33:29,625 --> 00:33:31,500
my mom thinks I'm a badass.

500
00:33:32,125 --> 00:33:33,916
I don't want her to know I'm a jackass.

501
00:33:35,750 --> 00:33:36,583
So what?

502
00:33:55,791 --> 00:33:56,833
Hello.

503
00:34:02,541 --> 00:34:04,500
Cherry, is that you?

504
00:34:05,875 --> 00:34:06,833
The line is busy.

505
00:34:11,625 --> 00:34:14,291
Now what?

506
00:34:24,875 --> 00:34:26,041
Hello.

507
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,083
I need a receipt.

508
00:34:34,625 --> 00:34:35,833
Thank you.

509
00:34:38,875 --> 00:34:41,416
I called all my friends,
but nobody answered.

510
00:34:41,500 --> 00:34:42,750
Don't worry.

511
00:34:43,750 --> 00:34:46,166
I will pay you back the ten grand.

512
00:34:49,791 --> 00:34:51,333
No hurry.

513
00:34:52,083 --> 00:34:53,750
Is the day after tomorrow okay?

514
00:34:58,625 --> 00:35:00,333
Day or night?

515
00:35:01,125 --> 00:35:02,291
Is the daytime too late?

516
00:35:03,166 --> 00:35:04,416
Before lunch, right?

517
00:35:05,916 --> 00:35:10,458
I'm joking. You can pay me back any time.

518
00:35:11,208 --> 00:35:13,208
-Why are you laughing?
-Nothing.

519
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:16,833
You loaned me the money.
Can you be my honey?

520
00:35:19,500 --> 00:35:20,958
Of course not. You have a boyfriend.

521
00:36:25,083 --> 00:36:27,833
-Where's Mom?
-She's delivering some laundry.

522
00:36:33,666 --> 00:36:36,250
-Somsak, same time tomorrow okay?
-Sure.

523
00:36:40,958 --> 00:36:42,291
What are you looking at?

524
00:36:42,666 --> 00:36:44,625
You look like
someone punched you in the face.

525
00:36:45,916 --> 00:36:48,083
No one punched me.

526
00:36:48,166 --> 00:36:49,250
I just tripped and fell.

527
00:36:49,333 --> 00:36:50,541
I see.

528
00:36:50,625 --> 00:36:53,833
You look like you got punched.

529
00:37:17,541 --> 00:37:18,750
Holy shit!

530
00:37:23,291 --> 00:37:24,125
What?

531
00:37:24,750 --> 00:37:26,375
It can't be fixed?

532
00:37:26,666 --> 00:37:28,541
How much is a new one?

533
00:37:29,416 --> 00:37:30,833
Really?

534
00:37:31,458 --> 00:37:35,375
Okay. Hold on. Let me ask my son.

535
00:37:42,791 --> 00:37:45,750
Josh, the repairman,
said it's too old to fix.

536
00:37:45,833 --> 00:37:47,916
Not worth it. It's bound to break again.

537
00:37:48,625 --> 00:37:50,083
We should buy a new one.

538
00:37:50,166 --> 00:37:53,541
A used one is 8,000.
With the repair service fee,

539
00:37:53,625 --> 00:37:54,666
we have to pay 12,000.

540
00:37:54,750 --> 00:37:55,916
What?

541
00:38:01,125 --> 00:38:05,375
If you don't have money,
I'll ask Josh to fix the old one.

542
00:38:07,333 --> 00:38:11,583
Who am I? I'm soon to be...

543
00:38:11,666 --> 00:38:14,125
an assistant manager at the bank.

544
00:38:16,166 --> 00:38:18,041
By the way,

545
00:38:18,125 --> 00:38:20,125
the cut looks pretty deep.

546
00:38:20,208 --> 00:38:21,708
Does it hurt?

547
00:38:23,333 --> 00:38:24,208
Yes, it hurts.

548
00:38:24,291 --> 00:38:26,541
You have to be more careful.

549
00:38:31,208 --> 00:38:32,416
I can't sit.

550
00:38:33,458 --> 00:38:36,333
My family needs the money.

551
00:38:36,416 --> 00:38:40,041
-Can I pay you back 1,000 baht a week?
-Sure, but with interest.

552
00:38:40,125 --> 00:38:43,583
But I don't mean money.
You have to give me free rides.

553
00:38:43,666 --> 00:38:46,416
Twice a week.

554
00:38:46,500 --> 00:38:49,625
Thank you. You are very kind.

555
00:38:49,708 --> 00:38:53,458
Yes, I am beautiful and kind.

556
00:38:57,041 --> 00:39:00,750
If you ever break up with your boyfriend,
I'm right here waiting.

557
00:39:03,250 --> 00:39:05,666
How sweet!

558
00:39:06,250 --> 00:39:10,000
I am so sweet that you can eat me up.

559
00:39:11,250 --> 00:39:13,291
Now you are pervy.

560
00:39:13,375 --> 00:39:17,208
Well, I'm not a funny guy.
I am a pervy guy.

561
00:39:17,291 --> 00:39:19,416
Gosh!

562
00:39:24,375 --> 00:39:27,125
You're free on Sunday, right?

563
00:39:27,750 --> 00:39:29,083
Yes, what's up?

564
00:39:29,166 --> 00:39:32,416
I'm cooking some curry.
Ask your friends from the bank to join us.

565
00:39:33,458 --> 00:39:34,458
And this time,

566
00:39:34,541 --> 00:39:35,791
don't bail on me.

567
00:39:35,875 --> 00:39:38,375
It happened too many times.
What a waste of food!

568
00:39:40,750 --> 00:39:42,208
Do you understand?

569
00:39:42,708 --> 00:39:43,791
Yes.

570
00:40:01,958 --> 00:40:05,041
This is Pakorn

571
00:40:05,125 --> 00:40:06,291
from the credit department.

572
00:40:06,791 --> 00:40:08,583
This is Ong-Art

573
00:40:08,666 --> 00:40:10,916
from the foreign currency...

574
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:12,083
department.

575
00:40:13,625 --> 00:40:15,583
Hi, ma'am.

576
00:40:15,666 --> 00:40:19,333
Very nice to meet you.

577
00:40:19,416 --> 00:40:22,125
Because at the bank,

578
00:40:22,208 --> 00:40:26,333
Sakrin always tells us about you.

579
00:40:27,583 --> 00:40:29,000
So, we...

580
00:40:29,083 --> 00:40:31,833
really wanted to visit you.

581
00:40:31,916 --> 00:40:33,208
But...

582
00:40:33,291 --> 00:40:34,708
in our department,

583
00:40:34,791 --> 00:40:37,458
we've been busy all the time.

584
00:40:37,541 --> 00:40:39,791
Taking care of...

585
00:40:39,875 --> 00:40:42,416
foreign currency,

586
00:40:42,500 --> 00:40:44,958
we really don't have free time.

587
00:40:45,041 --> 00:40:46,750
Foreign currency,

588
00:40:46,833 --> 00:40:48,291
American dollars or English pounds?

589
00:40:56,208 --> 00:40:59,791
Our bank doesn't mess
with those currencies,

590
00:41:00,375 --> 00:41:01,458
because...

591
00:41:01,541 --> 00:41:03,791
they fluctuate constantly.

592
00:41:03,875 --> 00:41:06,500
Rise and fall all the time.

593
00:41:07,583 --> 00:41:10,833
So we focus

594
00:41:10,916 --> 00:41:12,708
on the Myanmar kyats

595
00:41:12,791 --> 00:41:14,000
and Vietnamese dongs.

596
00:41:16,166 --> 00:41:17,833
For this quarter,

597
00:41:17,916 --> 00:41:20,333
our bank came up with a policy

598
00:41:20,416 --> 00:41:23,500
to sell all the kyats and dongs.

599
00:41:23,583 --> 00:41:29,166
Then we will focus on the Indian rupee.

600
00:41:29,875 --> 00:41:30,791
It is clear now.

601
00:41:33,958 --> 00:41:35,375
Sak,

602
00:41:35,666 --> 00:41:37,291
come with me.

603
00:41:44,666 --> 00:41:45,875
Yes, Mom.

604
00:41:50,750 --> 00:41:52,041
You guys giggle a lot.

605
00:41:52,125 --> 00:41:53,916
-Right, sir.
-Did you smoke some weed?

606
00:41:55,083 --> 00:41:57,250
The weather is very nice today.

607
00:41:57,875 --> 00:42:00,666
-Indian Rupee?
-Yes, sir.

608
00:42:04,833 --> 00:42:05,791
Are you sure?

609
00:42:06,750 --> 00:42:07,833
About what?

610
00:42:08,125 --> 00:42:10,458
That they work at the same place as you.

611
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:13,166
Why did you say that?

612
00:42:14,708 --> 00:42:17,750
He asked, so I answered.

613
00:42:17,833 --> 00:42:19,500
You really fucked up.

614
00:42:20,500 --> 00:42:22,625
What did you expect?

615
00:42:23,583 --> 00:42:24,833
Want some drugs?

616
00:42:25,375 --> 00:42:28,583
-I quit a long time ago.
-Not for you.

617
00:42:28,916 --> 00:42:30,500
I mean, we give him a drug.

618
00:42:31,458 --> 00:42:32,875
What drug?

619
00:42:34,458 --> 00:42:37,458
Here, speed.

620
00:42:37,541 --> 00:42:39,416
Why?

621
00:42:40,333 --> 00:42:43,791
Ong-Art and Pakorn
don't look like bankers to you?

622
00:42:43,875 --> 00:42:48,791
Not even a little,
especially that Ong-Art guy.

623
00:42:48,875 --> 00:42:52,708
Sak told me this old man loves
to find faults in other people.

624
00:42:52,791 --> 00:42:55,000
So what?

625
00:42:55,083 --> 00:42:57,291
If he takes this drug,

626
00:42:57,375 --> 00:43:00,833
he'll be busy with something else.
He'll stop scrutinizing us.

627
00:43:00,916 --> 00:43:04,208
Suree, you don't buy this either?

628
00:43:05,791 --> 00:43:08,000
You don't have to answer.

629
00:43:08,083 --> 00:43:12,958
You just question your boy.
I will interrogate those two.

630
00:43:13,625 --> 00:43:16,041
Why am I here?

631
00:43:29,791 --> 00:43:31,541
Just in time.

632
00:43:35,875 --> 00:43:37,291
Wow!

633
00:43:37,375 --> 00:43:40,041
-What a beautiful watch you have!
-It's Rado's.

634
00:43:40,125 --> 00:43:42,208
Gold case, same model as George Clooney's.

635
00:43:46,916 --> 00:43:49,791
The weather like this, I think...

636
00:43:50,541 --> 00:43:52,500
we should have a drink.

637
00:43:52,833 --> 00:43:54,083
It would be...

638
00:43:54,166 --> 00:43:56,916
an honor for us.

639
00:44:03,375 --> 00:44:04,708
Wait!

640
00:44:04,791 --> 00:44:07,291
Did you put a drug in here?

641
00:44:07,708 --> 00:44:09,041
I'm an ex-cop, you know?

642
00:44:09,125 --> 00:44:11,583
The smell can't trick my nose.

643
00:44:13,708 --> 00:44:16,916
Mr. Ex-Cop,

644
00:44:17,458 --> 00:44:19,833
if you are skeptical,

645
00:44:19,916 --> 00:44:20,958
I will...

646
00:44:21,041 --> 00:44:23,000
drink first.

647
00:44:36,583 --> 00:44:38,000
Your turn.

648
00:44:50,583 --> 00:44:52,791
-You once told me.
-What?

649
00:44:52,875 --> 00:44:54,666
Don't judge a book by its cover.

650
00:44:58,375 --> 00:45:01,625
Though Ong-Art looks like that,

651
00:45:01,708 --> 00:45:03,708
he's one of the best we have.

652
00:45:03,791 --> 00:45:04,916
Really?

653
00:45:05,541 --> 00:45:06,416
Yeah.

654
00:45:08,666 --> 00:45:09,625
Okay.

655
00:45:10,458 --> 00:45:12,125
I believe you.

656
00:45:16,708 --> 00:45:18,500
What's happening to me?

657
00:45:19,916 --> 00:45:21,833
Why do I want to work this much?

658
00:45:27,583 --> 00:45:28,750
The house looks very messy.

659
00:45:28,833 --> 00:45:31,291
It's dusty everywhere. God damn it!

660
00:45:31,375 --> 00:45:33,500
I can't stand it.
This is no place to live.

661
00:45:40,250 --> 00:45:41,916
I have to do something.

662
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:44,375
-The pill is too strong.
-Hold on.

663
00:45:44,458 --> 00:45:46,291
I can't.

664
00:45:46,375 --> 00:45:48,250
You have to throw up.

665
00:45:48,333 --> 00:45:51,000
This is like a country house.
All the dust from the road.

666
00:45:51,083 --> 00:45:54,166
Drivers just don't care.
Young man, are you cold?

667
00:45:54,250 --> 00:45:55,500
It's windy here.

668
00:45:57,000 --> 00:45:59,125
You probably ate too much. I forgot.

669
00:45:59,208 --> 00:46:00,375
When you iron,

670
00:46:00,458 --> 00:46:02,500
you have to drench the clothes
like when you fry grasshopper.

671
00:46:02,583 --> 00:46:05,541
So the clothes will be fragrant
and good for wearing.

672
00:46:06,958 --> 00:46:09,083
Young man, you want me to iron your suit?

673
00:46:09,166 --> 00:46:11,083
Take it off and I will take care of it.

674
00:46:11,166 --> 00:46:13,000
I'll get you some water.

675
00:46:13,083 --> 00:46:14,375
Sewing machines

676
00:46:14,458 --> 00:46:17,000
are not only for women,
men can use them, too.

677
00:46:17,083 --> 00:46:18,541
Whether patching, mending,

678
00:46:18,625 --> 00:46:20,000
or stitching, it's as easy as pie.

679
00:46:20,083 --> 00:46:22,541
I grew up
in the Thai Toray Tetoron factory.

680
00:46:22,625 --> 00:46:24,708
Rinse your mouth.

681
00:46:26,291 --> 00:46:27,333
My hand!

682
00:46:27,416 --> 00:46:29,041
God damn it!

683
00:46:29,125 --> 00:46:32,208
It's okay. I shed very little blood.

684
00:46:32,750 --> 00:46:34,583
What a big mess! I have to mop the floor.

685
00:46:36,166 --> 00:46:37,708
Rinse some more.

686
00:46:37,791 --> 00:46:40,166
When you mop the floor,
no need to change the water.

687
00:46:40,250 --> 00:46:42,208
One bucket is enough. Don't waste water.

688
00:46:42,875 --> 00:46:44,541
More. More.

689
00:46:47,791 --> 00:46:49,750
Feeling better?

690
00:46:50,041 --> 00:46:51,583
I told you not to drink it.

691
00:46:52,916 --> 00:46:53,833
This is not helping.

692
00:46:53,916 --> 00:46:56,916
Maybe I have to go swimming.
I have too much energy.

693
00:47:04,583 --> 00:47:05,666
What is going on?

694
00:47:06,125 --> 00:47:08,666
Nothing. The heat got to him.

695
00:47:30,708 --> 00:47:31,916
Sakrin.

696
00:48:05,708 --> 00:48:06,958
Sakrin!

697
00:49:04,833 --> 00:49:05,791
Hi!

698
00:49:07,375 --> 00:49:08,875
What are you doing here?

699
00:49:09,333 --> 00:49:11,333
Why did you call me?

700
00:49:11,416 --> 00:49:12,916
I saw a guy.

701
00:49:13,291 --> 00:49:16,333
He looked just like you,

702
00:49:16,416 --> 00:49:18,208
but he was wearing an office uniform.

703
00:49:18,833 --> 00:49:19,708
Yeah?

704
00:49:20,791 --> 00:49:22,833
I took my eyes off him for one second,
and he's gone.

705
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:27,083
What are you doing here?

706
00:49:27,416 --> 00:49:30,541
I dropped off my regular customer.

707
00:49:31,375 --> 00:49:32,916
Then I picked up some stuff.

708
00:49:35,250 --> 00:49:36,583
Why do you look exhausted?

709
00:49:37,083 --> 00:49:38,125
The stuff is heavy.

710
00:49:38,458 --> 00:49:40,416
-You're sweating a lot, too.
-It's hot today.

711
00:49:54,750 --> 00:49:56,500
Hello, baby!

712
00:50:02,166 --> 00:50:03,666
I don't understand.

713
00:50:03,750 --> 00:50:07,625
I told you to deliver all these papers.

714
00:50:07,708 --> 00:50:09,458
How many times
will you make the same mistake?

715
00:50:09,541 --> 00:50:11,208
I didn't mean it, baby.

716
00:50:12,541 --> 00:50:16,291
How many times have I told you
not to call me baby at work?

717
00:50:16,375 --> 00:50:17,708
Four times.

718
00:50:17,791 --> 00:50:18,666
Wow!

719
00:50:18,750 --> 00:50:21,041
You asked me to note it down.

720
00:50:25,333 --> 00:50:26,875
The first time,

721
00:50:26,958 --> 00:50:29,500
I wanted it sent to Salaya branch.
Where did it go?

722
00:50:29,583 --> 00:50:31,166
Pattaya.

723
00:50:33,375 --> 00:50:34,208
The second time,

724
00:50:34,291 --> 00:50:36,583
I wanted it sent to Horkanka.
Where did it go?

725
00:50:36,666 --> 00:50:37,833
Saochingcha.

726
00:50:39,958 --> 00:50:43,041
Well noted. Just how I taught you.

727
00:50:44,250 --> 00:50:45,208
They sound similar.

728
00:50:45,291 --> 00:50:46,625
Don't.

729
00:50:46,708 --> 00:50:47,541
But I--

730
00:50:47,625 --> 00:50:48,750
No, no.

731
00:50:49,583 --> 00:50:50,458
Especially when--

732
00:50:50,541 --> 00:50:54,208
Hush...

733
00:50:54,958 --> 00:50:58,041
If you can't do simple tasks,

734
00:50:58,458 --> 00:51:00,250
you'll be a teller forever, won't you?

735
00:51:03,250 --> 00:51:04,541
Use your brain.

736
00:51:23,333 --> 00:51:25,083
Are you okay?

737
00:51:27,500 --> 00:51:28,916
Not okay.

738
00:51:40,208 --> 00:51:41,416
Eat up.

739
00:51:44,416 --> 00:51:48,250
It's strange
when your boss is your boyfriend.

740
00:51:48,625 --> 00:51:50,500
When he scolds me,
I don't know how to feel,

741
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:52,833
scared for being scolded by a boss,

742
00:51:53,291 --> 00:51:55,375
or hurt for being scolded by a boyfriend.

743
00:51:59,791 --> 00:52:01,208
Have you been together long?

744
00:52:01,583 --> 00:52:05,166
Quite long, since college years.

745
00:52:05,833 --> 00:52:08,041
He was my senior.

746
00:52:08,458 --> 00:52:09,791
He led the college's cheer squad.

747
00:52:10,250 --> 00:52:11,666
He was a runner, also.

748
00:52:12,875 --> 00:52:13,708
A runner?

749
00:52:13,791 --> 00:52:14,916
Yeah.

750
00:52:15,875 --> 00:52:18,208
-You don't believe it, right?
-Wow!

751
00:52:20,708 --> 00:52:22,416
Let me see.

752
00:52:28,416 --> 00:52:29,750
Sorry.

753
00:52:29,833 --> 00:52:32,625
That's okay.
Everyone has the same reaction.

754
00:52:32,708 --> 00:52:34,000
He's very different now, right? 

755
00:52:34,083 --> 00:52:36,791
-Just a little.
-Liar!

756
00:52:38,375 --> 00:52:41,833
Why do you always say things
like words on bumper stickers?

757
00:52:44,458 --> 00:52:46,291
When I say them out loud...

758
00:52:47,458 --> 00:52:50,041
they give me courage.

759
00:52:50,125 --> 00:52:52,041
And more importantly...

760
00:52:53,291 --> 00:52:54,916
I can text them as pickup lines.

761
00:52:57,708 --> 00:52:58,750
What did you send?

762
00:53:12,375 --> 00:53:13,458
YOU HAVE RECEIVED A PAYMENT

763
00:53:15,041 --> 00:53:16,541
Nice!

764
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:19,583
I thought you sent me a cheesy line.

765
00:53:22,916 --> 00:53:24,791
What if I really had
sent you a cheesy line?

766
00:53:38,541 --> 00:53:39,458
Hello?

767
00:53:40,208 --> 00:53:41,875
Now?

768
00:53:41,958 --> 00:53:43,333
Okay.

769
00:53:46,875 --> 00:53:48,416
I have to go to work now.

770
00:53:48,500 --> 00:53:49,500
What job?

771
00:53:49,916 --> 00:53:52,041
-Delivering some stuff at a carnival.
-Take me with you.

772
00:53:52,750 --> 00:53:54,000
Check, please.

773
00:53:57,000 --> 00:53:58,666
No, let me treat you.

774
00:54:05,208 --> 00:54:06,625
Eight hundred and twenty baht.

775
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:15,416
It's okay.

776
00:54:15,916 --> 00:54:16,958
We can split it.

777
00:54:22,125 --> 00:54:24,500
The gesture makes me happy enough.

778
00:54:25,625 --> 00:54:29,166
How about you pay 420,

779
00:54:29,250 --> 00:54:31,458
and I pay 400? You treat me 20 baht, okay?

780
00:54:34,166 --> 00:54:35,083
Okay.

781
00:54:45,875 --> 00:54:47,208
How nice!

782
00:54:47,291 --> 00:54:48,416
What's nice?

783
00:54:48,500 --> 00:54:50,333
Usually, I order pork barbeque.

784
00:54:50,416 --> 00:54:52,833
I've never delivered it before. It's fun.

785
00:54:52,916 --> 00:54:54,958
Next time can you deliver it to my house?

786
00:54:56,875 --> 00:54:58,416
Give me one free set.

787
00:54:58,500 --> 00:55:01,750
I will ask the owner for you.

788
00:55:13,083 --> 00:55:15,250
HAUNTED HOUSE

789
00:55:30,500 --> 00:55:32,208
Sakrin.

790
00:55:32,291 --> 00:55:35,500
You know what? I love your job.

791
00:55:35,583 --> 00:55:36,416
Why?

792
00:55:36,791 --> 00:55:39,708
You can go anywhere you want.

793
00:55:39,791 --> 00:55:42,375
Not like me.
I have to sit in the bank all day.

794
00:55:45,458 --> 00:55:47,875
But I'm the kind of person
who's scared of everything.

795
00:55:48,750 --> 00:55:51,500
I only stay in my safe zone.

796
00:55:51,583 --> 00:55:54,625
I thought of quitting the job often.

797
00:55:54,708 --> 00:55:56,375
Several times a day.

798
00:55:56,458 --> 00:55:58,166
I never have the guts to do it.

799
00:55:59,208 --> 00:56:01,666
But when it's time,

800
00:56:01,750 --> 00:56:02,708
I will quit.

801
00:56:02,791 --> 00:56:04,083
What will you do?

802
00:56:09,708 --> 00:56:10,833
What's that?

803
00:56:11,625 --> 00:56:13,583
CAPTAIN JAI

804
00:56:14,750 --> 00:56:15,875
Am I crazy?

805
00:56:18,916 --> 00:56:22,416
I'm so fed up with uneducated people.

806
00:56:22,500 --> 00:56:26,416
You don't even know how to use a toy gun,
how can you make a living?

807
00:56:28,208 --> 00:56:29,291
It's really easy.

808
00:56:29,958 --> 00:56:30,958
Here!

809
00:56:32,333 --> 00:56:35,083
Keep it down.

810
00:56:35,458 --> 00:56:38,333
I said keep the gun down, not your head.

811
00:56:38,416 --> 00:56:39,750
I guess you want me to

812
00:56:39,833 --> 00:56:41,458
-beat you up.
-Norasingh!

813
00:56:41,541 --> 00:56:44,750
She's our customer.
Can't you spare a child?

814
00:56:44,833 --> 00:56:47,291
Go get some wet dolls.
These dolls are already dry.

815
00:56:47,375 --> 00:56:48,333
Go!

816
00:56:48,833 --> 00:56:51,333
Little miss, you shouldn't play with guns.

817
00:56:51,416 --> 00:56:54,208
You better go
to the lucky draw booth over there.

818
00:56:55,375 --> 00:56:57,416
Shooting game!

819
00:56:57,875 --> 00:57:00,291
Wow!

820
00:57:01,250 --> 00:57:03,666
-Let's go.
-I don't think it's a good idea.

821
00:57:04,166 --> 00:57:06,458
Why not? Let's go.

822
00:57:06,541 --> 00:57:07,833
No.

823
