My nephew's name is Suchart.

1091
01:14:02,083 --> 01:14:03,916
He also works here.

1092
01:14:04,000 --> 01:14:04,916
Do you know him?

1093
01:14:07,166 --> 01:14:09,625
-The guy in the glasses?
-He doesn't wear glasses.

1094
01:14:14,250 --> 01:14:16,916
That's him, my nephew.

1095
01:14:18,958 --> 01:14:20,458
Ae, come here.

1096
01:14:36,458 --> 01:14:38,416
That's Suree.

1097
01:14:38,500 --> 01:14:40,125
Wonderful! Now we all can meet.

1098
01:14:54,000 --> 01:14:54,833
Sak.

1099
01:15:08,958 --> 01:15:11,291
-Hello, Director.
-Hi.

1100
01:15:13,541 --> 01:15:15,416
Where is Mrs. Pranee's paper?

1101
01:15:17,208 --> 01:15:18,875
Is it in the car?

1102
01:15:20,916 --> 01:15:22,625
Remember? Mrs. Pranee.

1103
01:15:22,708 --> 01:15:23,916
Which Pranee?

1104
01:15:24,000 --> 01:15:25,375
That Pranee.

1105
01:15:25,458 --> 01:15:28,750
Pranee, Pranee.

1106
01:15:28,833 --> 01:15:29,666
Pranee!

1107
01:15:30,625 --> 01:15:32,375
Please excuse us.

1108
01:15:37,666 --> 01:15:39,416
Uncle, you know that guy?

1109
01:15:40,083 --> 01:15:42,041
He's my friend's son.

1110
01:15:49,208 --> 01:15:50,041
Wittaya,

1111
01:15:50,125 --> 01:15:51,583
where did Sak go?

1112
01:15:51,666 --> 01:15:53,750
He said he had some work to do.

1113
01:16:07,166 --> 01:16:10,666
Sakrin. What the hell is going on?
You have to explain everything.

1114
01:16:18,583 --> 01:16:20,625
I graduated almost a year ago.

1115
01:16:22,083 --> 01:16:25,250
I applied for a job at several places.

1116
01:16:25,333 --> 01:16:27,208
They all rejected me.

1117
01:16:28,666 --> 01:16:30,875
That's why I work as a bikeman.

1118
01:16:32,583 --> 01:16:34,416
I'm the only son in the house.

1119
01:16:35,375 --> 01:16:37,208
I can't make any of them proud.

1120
01:16:37,916 --> 01:16:40,416
Why do you want to work in a bank?

1121
01:16:40,500 --> 01:16:41,791
It's not a cool job.

1122
01:16:41,875 --> 01:16:43,583
People these days don't think that way.

1123
01:16:43,666 --> 01:16:45,125
I don't care about others.

1124
01:16:45,916 --> 01:16:50,750
It's not important
how other people think these days.

1125
01:16:51,416 --> 01:16:53,791
My dad used to be a banker.

1126
01:16:55,666 --> 01:16:57,666
He used to work in a bank.

1127
01:16:58,166 --> 01:17:00,250
He was everything for us.

1128
01:17:01,000 --> 01:17:05,083
He provided for us.
Mom and Grandma used to live well.

1129
01:17:08,375 --> 01:17:10,083
When my mom looked at him,

1130
01:17:10,708 --> 01:17:13,000
it was obvious how she felt.

1131
01:17:13,708 --> 01:17:14,791
Now that he's gone,

1132
01:17:14,875 --> 01:17:17,208
everything's changed.

1133
01:17:17,625 --> 01:17:21,666
I want my mom to be proud of me
the way she was proud of my dad.

1134
01:17:21,750 --> 01:17:24,166
How long are you going to keep lying?

1135
01:17:24,916 --> 01:17:26,541
I don't know.

1136
01:17:26,625 --> 01:17:27,958
But...

1137
01:17:28,041 --> 01:17:29,666
I don't know what to do either.

1138
01:17:30,000 --> 01:17:32,083
Don't lie, then. Tell them the truth.

1139
01:17:33,958 --> 01:17:35,875
I'd rather die.

1140
01:17:35,958 --> 01:17:37,458
You are overreacting.

1141
01:17:37,541 --> 01:17:40,416
The truth will never die.
It's okay to tell the truth.

1142
01:17:42,458 --> 01:17:44,208
You are not my family,
you don't understand.

1143
01:17:47,416 --> 01:17:48,291
So what now?

1144
01:17:51,041 --> 01:17:54,208
Are you going to be a biker
who pretends to be a banker forever?

1145
01:17:54,291 --> 01:17:57,083
-That's a stupid idea.
-Yes, it's stupid.

1146
01:17:57,166 --> 01:17:59,125
You don't know what I've been through.

1147
01:17:59,208 --> 01:18:00,958
I sent my resume to dozens of places.

1148
01:18:01,333 --> 01:18:04,541
Three times to TMB, four times to SCB,
twice to Kasikorn Bank,

1149
01:18:04,625 --> 01:18:06,791
five times to Bangkok Bank,
six times to GSB, once to Krungsri Bank.

1150
01:18:06,875 --> 01:18:08,750
They all rejected me.

1151
01:18:09,166 --> 01:18:12,416
I partnered up with a friend.
He took the money and left.

1152
01:18:12,750 --> 01:18:16,250
It's not like I want to be
a poor bikeman for the rest of my life.

1153
01:18:21,833 --> 01:18:23,208
Whatever.

1154
01:18:24,708 --> 01:18:26,416
You wouldn't understand.

1155
01:18:27,083 --> 01:18:29,250
Right, I don't understand.

1156
01:18:30,083 --> 01:18:33,458
I don't understand
why I care for a loser like you.

1157
01:18:41,458 --> 01:18:43,250
Now I know your secret.

1158
01:18:43,333 --> 01:18:45,208
I will tell everyone.

1159
01:18:45,291 --> 01:18:48,833
I'm really drunk.
Let's go home before anybody catches us.

1160
01:18:48,916 --> 01:18:50,708
Where did that bastard go?

1161
01:18:58,291 --> 01:18:59,708
You bumped into him.

1162
01:18:59,791 --> 01:19:01,208
Is he dead?

1163
01:19:03,125 --> 01:19:04,416
I don't know if he's dead,

1164
01:19:05,083 --> 01:19:06,541
but he peed his pants.

1165
01:19:10,000 --> 01:19:13,541
Shit. He should have pissed
in the toilet first.

1166
01:19:20,875 --> 01:19:22,000
I'm sorry.

1167
01:19:22,083 --> 01:19:23,666
I know I'm at fault.

1168
01:19:23,750 --> 01:19:24,833
SAKRIN

1169
01:19:31,958 --> 01:19:35,291
If you don't forgive me,
I will keep apologizing.

1170
01:19:42,583 --> 01:19:45,500
Doctor, will he survive?

1171
01:19:45,583 --> 01:19:47,250
He is safe now.

1172
01:19:47,666 --> 01:19:50,166
Then why is his tongue like that?

1173
01:19:50,250 --> 01:19:51,958
It's a side effect.

1174
01:20:08,500 --> 01:20:10,583
You agreed to see me.
You're not angry anymore?

1175
01:20:11,416 --> 01:20:12,333
Wrong.

1176
01:20:14,416 --> 01:20:16,791
But I have something important
to say to you.

1177
01:20:17,708 --> 01:20:19,291
Listen.

1178
01:20:19,375 --> 01:20:21,333
If you are afraid to tell the truth,

1179
01:20:21,416 --> 01:20:23,541
why don't you make it a reality?

1180
01:20:26,916 --> 01:20:28,083
Try again.

1181
01:20:28,166 --> 01:20:30,958
NORTH CHINA BANK
AVAILABLE POSITIONS

1182
01:20:33,875 --> 01:20:35,291
I've tried 21 times.

1183
01:20:35,583 --> 01:20:38,083
How do you know
you won't succeed the next time?

1184
01:20:41,750 --> 01:20:42,583
Listen.

1185
01:20:42,666 --> 01:20:45,166
A lie is like a bandage.

1186
01:20:45,250 --> 01:20:47,791
It can cover up the wound,
but it will never heal it.

1187
01:20:47,875 --> 01:20:50,291
Do you want to keep that wound
for the rest of your life?

1188
01:20:51,083 --> 01:20:52,625
You can say cheesy things, too?

1189
01:20:54,208 --> 01:20:55,833
Don't change the subject.

1190
01:20:57,333 --> 01:21:00,500
I will tutor you. Okay?

1191
01:21:04,250 --> 01:21:05,208
Fight!

1192
01:21:05,750 --> 01:21:06,916
Fight!

1193
01:21:08,083 --> 01:21:09,458
We're starting now?

1194
01:21:11,791 --> 01:21:14,166
You can use this conversation
with Chinese customers.

1195
01:21:14,250 --> 01:21:16,750
Our bank has Chinese customers.

1196
01:21:25,083 --> 01:21:27,541
Have you left the house?

1197
01:21:27,625 --> 01:21:30,916
Soon. Almost ready.
Let's meet at the station.

1198
01:21:31,000 --> 01:21:33,250
Don't forget your book.

1199
01:21:33,333 --> 01:21:35,916
I won't forget it.

1200
01:22:18,750 --> 01:22:20,208
TYPE YOUR NUMBER TO CHECK THE RESULT

1201
01:22:20,291 --> 01:22:21,791
DOWNLOADING

1202
01:22:23,541 --> 01:22:25,875
The Internet is slow.

1203
01:22:30,333 --> 01:22:31,875
Want to try again?

1204
01:22:43,375 --> 01:22:45,208
YOU DID NOT GET THIS POSITION

1205
01:22:51,708 --> 01:22:56,625
The page might not be working properly.
I will check at the bank again tomorrow.

1206
01:22:57,375 --> 01:22:58,791
It's okay.

1207
01:22:58,875 --> 01:23:00,541
You don't need to check it.

1208
01:23:02,333 --> 01:23:03,583
I didn't get the job.

1209
01:23:42,375 --> 01:23:45,250
Hello! What's up?

1210
01:23:45,333 --> 01:23:47,541
Ae is going to your house.

1211
01:23:47,625 --> 01:23:48,875
What?

1212
01:23:56,791 --> 01:23:57,791
Mom.

1213
01:24:00,416 --> 01:24:01,875
You are blocking the TV, you know?

1214
01:24:03,291 --> 01:24:04,500
I know.

1215
01:24:08,708 --> 01:24:10,833
She just doesn't care.

1216
01:24:55,750 --> 01:24:56,916
Ma'am,

1217
01:24:57,000 --> 01:25:00,333
do you know your son...

1218
01:25:00,916 --> 01:25:02,583
is a liar,

1219
01:25:02,666 --> 01:25:03,916
a fraud.

1220
01:25:05,375 --> 01:25:08,416
Who? Who is a fraud?

1221
01:25:09,833 --> 01:25:11,000
Your son.

1222
01:25:38,541 --> 01:25:42,458
The reason I'm here today
is that I want you to know the truth.

1223
01:25:42,541 --> 01:25:45,500
Your son is a liar.

1224
01:25:45,583 --> 01:25:47,500
He did many bad things.

1225
01:25:47,583 --> 01:25:50,166
What did you say? Come again.

1226
01:25:51,958 --> 01:25:53,000
From the beginning?

1227
01:25:53,083 --> 01:25:54,083
Yes.

1228
01:25:56,000 --> 01:25:57,000
Ma'am.

1229
01:25:57,416 --> 01:26:00,833
I'm here to tell you...

1230
01:26:00,916 --> 01:26:04,166
your son lies about everything.

1231
01:26:04,250 --> 01:26:06,000
He lies to his salami.

1232
01:26:06,083 --> 01:26:07,625
What salami?

1233
01:26:07,708 --> 01:26:09,791
I'm not talking about salami.

1234
01:26:09,875 --> 01:26:11,666
I meant his family.

1235
01:26:11,750 --> 01:26:14,375
He lies about everything to everyone.

1236
01:26:14,458 --> 01:26:18,500
He just keeps lying
and making a big mess, ma'am.

1237
01:26:18,583 --> 01:26:19,500
All right.

1238
01:26:21,500 --> 01:26:22,500
Write it down.

1239
01:26:24,208 --> 01:26:25,166
Thank you.

1240
01:26:26,041 --> 01:26:28,333
-Ma'am.
-I said write it down.

1241
01:26:29,416 --> 01:26:30,541
Right.

1242
01:27:01,000 --> 01:27:01,833
Serves you right!

1243
01:27:01,916 --> 01:27:03,583
A liar like you!

1244
01:27:04,083 --> 01:27:07,125
The truth is you are just a lowly bikeman.

1245
01:27:07,208 --> 01:27:08,416
Asshole.

1246
01:27:08,500 --> 01:27:09,625
Stop pretending.

1247
01:27:18,375 --> 01:27:19,416
Mom!

1248
01:27:19,500 --> 01:27:20,708
Grandma!

1249
01:27:21,708 --> 01:27:23,208
Grandma is dead.

1250
01:27:29,541 --> 01:27:31,708
Going through the market
takes seven minutes.

1251
01:27:31,791 --> 01:27:33,000
What are you talking about?

1252
01:27:33,083 --> 01:27:35,500
I am calculating the best route.

1253
01:27:35,583 --> 01:27:37,333
Crossing the railway will take...

1254
01:27:37,416 --> 01:27:38,791
-five minutes.
-What?

1255
01:27:39,541 --> 01:27:41,958
Sak! It's a curve!

1256
01:27:46,333 --> 01:27:47,166
Sak!

1257
01:27:51,291 --> 01:27:52,333
Truck!

1258
01:27:57,875 --> 01:27:59,416
A train's coming!

1259
01:28:29,041 --> 01:28:29,958
Sak!

1260
01:28:30,041 --> 01:28:32,708
Let's go. What are you waiting for?

1261
01:28:38,083 --> 01:28:40,250
HOSPITAL

1262
01:28:44,541 --> 01:28:47,541
ACCIDENT AND EMERGENCY

1263
01:28:57,625 --> 01:28:59,833
ACCIDENT AND EMERGENCY

1264
01:29:05,916 --> 01:29:07,250
I'm sorry.

1265
01:29:09,750 --> 01:29:12,625
I don't want you to feel embarrassed...

1266
01:29:12,708 --> 01:29:14,916
that your son is just a bikeman.

1267
01:29:19,208 --> 01:29:20,791
I'm not embarrassed.

1268
01:29:21,708 --> 01:29:24,583
But I'm angry that you lied to me
for a long time.

1269
01:29:24,666 --> 01:29:27,166
Why didn't you tell me
before that jerk did?

1270
01:29:27,250 --> 01:29:30,166
Though it was bad, your grandmother and I
would've still felt better than this

1271
01:29:30,250 --> 01:29:32,875
if you had told us yourself.

1272
01:29:37,000 --> 01:29:38,083
We all...

1273
01:29:38,750 --> 01:29:41,166
have lied to others at some point.

1274
01:29:44,291 --> 01:29:45,958
I also lied to you.

1275
01:29:47,958 --> 01:29:50,291
The day after the party at the bank,

1276
01:29:50,375 --> 01:29:54,375
I bought a train ticket and followed you.

1277
01:30:49,708 --> 01:30:55,500
FOR MOM

1278
01:31:03,541 --> 01:31:07,208
You might be embarrassed
that you are a bikeman,

1279
01:31:07,291 --> 01:31:10,666
but I'm not.

1280
01:31:14,500 --> 01:31:16,583
The way you are not picky about jobs...

1281
01:31:17,000 --> 01:31:20,291
you're doing your best
to support the family.

1282
01:31:20,375 --> 01:31:23,708
I think it's too cool and admirable
to be embarrassed about it.

1283
01:31:33,250 --> 01:31:34,166
Honey,

1284
01:31:34,500 --> 01:31:37,125
I am proud of you. You know that?

1285
01:31:49,208 --> 01:31:52,583
Believe me. If your dad were here...

1286
01:31:53,916 --> 01:31:56,541
he'd have said the same.

1287
01:32:20,583 --> 01:32:22,208
As for your grandmother,

1288
01:32:22,708 --> 01:32:25,000
you can apologize to her later.

1289
01:32:48,291 --> 01:32:50,500
These are the medical expenses
up to today.

1290
01:33:35,875 --> 01:33:37,958
BALANCE: 7,423 BAHT

1291
01:33:51,500 --> 01:33:54,875
I heard your grandma's in the hospital
and you don't have any money.

1292
01:33:55,541 --> 01:33:57,416
So I want to help out.

1293
01:33:57,500 --> 01:33:59,750
-How would you help me?
-What a question!

1294
01:33:59,833 --> 01:34:01,416
I'll help you pay the bill.

1295
01:34:01,500 --> 01:34:02,875
That's okay.

1296
01:34:03,500 --> 01:34:04,666
You don't need to.

1297
01:34:05,208 --> 01:34:06,958
But I want to help.

1298
01:34:07,875 --> 01:34:10,375
I'm already here.

1299
01:34:13,875 --> 01:34:15,041
Hi!

1300
01:34:16,750 --> 01:34:18,000
How did you get here?

1301
01:34:18,083 --> 01:34:20,625
The same way you commute.

1302
01:34:20,708 --> 01:34:23,125
I'll hang up now.
It's wasting phone credit.

1303
01:34:28,833 --> 01:34:31,291
How did you know
my grandmother was in the hospital?

1304
01:34:32,458 --> 01:34:34,291
Everybody knows.

1305
01:34:35,291 --> 01:34:39,583
Thank you, but you don't need to help.
The bill is...

1306
01:34:39,666 --> 01:34:40,625
too expensive.

1307
01:34:47,875 --> 01:34:50,458
Told you it's expensive.

1308
01:34:51,958 --> 01:34:54,333
There must be a way.

1309
01:34:57,208 --> 01:34:58,250
Look over there.

1310
01:34:59,708 --> 01:35:01,083
There!

1311
01:35:25,750 --> 01:35:29,208
Hey, bro!

1312
01:35:30,166 --> 01:35:32,875
I heard you don't have enough money.

1313
01:35:32,958 --> 01:35:34,333
So, we...

1314
01:35:34,416 --> 01:35:36,041
brought you some.

1315
01:35:37,708 --> 01:35:38,916
Give you.

1316
01:35:39,000 --> 01:35:42,583
I and my friends.

1317
01:35:46,083 --> 01:35:47,291
Open.

1318
01:35:51,833 --> 01:35:53,458
Where did you get the money from?

1319
01:35:55,666 --> 01:35:57,791
How dare you ask that?

1320
01:35:59,000 --> 01:36:01,166
Do I look poor to you?

1321
01:36:01,250 --> 01:36:03,000
You look penniless.

1322
01:36:04,625 --> 01:36:06,083
Listen to him.

1323
01:36:06,166 --> 01:36:07,791
I shouldn't have asked.

1324
01:36:09,583 --> 01:36:11,041
So where did you get the money from?

1325
01:36:11,125 --> 01:36:13,375
Fast cash

1326
01:36:13,458 --> 01:36:16,625
and a new bike to ride here.

1327
01:36:18,375 --> 01:36:19,625
FAST CASH

1328
01:36:21,875 --> 01:36:22,708
APPROVED

1329
01:36:24,541 --> 01:36:25,958
Take it.

1330
01:36:26,041 --> 01:36:28,458
You can pay us back when you can.

1331
01:36:28,791 --> 01:36:31,083
But...

1332
01:36:31,458 --> 01:36:34,000
No "but" between true friends.

1333
01:36:35,125 --> 01:36:38,291
Though we are lowly bikemen,

1334
01:36:38,375 --> 01:36:42,291
you can trust
we are as good a friend as any.

1335
01:36:50,208 --> 01:36:53,833
-How's that?
-You are very cool.

1336
01:37:16,958 --> 01:37:17,791
Hello.

1337
01:37:17,875 --> 01:37:20,875
Hello. I'm calling from SCB.
May I speak to Mr. Sakrin?

1338
01:37:20,958 --> 01:37:21,916
Speaking.

1339
01:37:22,000 --> 01:37:24,166
Our bank has a position available.

1340
01:37:24,250 --> 01:37:27,500
We would like to invite you
to work with us.

1341
01:37:27,583 --> 01:37:28,791
What did you say?

1342
01:37:28,875 --> 01:37:32,416
You are the first on our waiting list,
so we chose you.

1343
01:37:32,500 --> 01:37:34,541
-Really?
-Yes.

1344
01:37:34,625 --> 01:37:37,458
Can you start working next week?

1345
01:37:39,166 --> 01:37:40,958
Next week?

1346
01:37:43,041 --> 01:37:45,250
Yes, definitely.

1347
01:37:45,333 --> 01:37:48,125
Okay. See you. Bye.

1348
01:37:48,208 --> 01:37:49,541
Bye.

1349
01:37:57,166 --> 01:37:59,041
What are you grinning about, Sak?

1350
01:37:59,125 --> 01:38:01,208
The bank has a position available.

1351
01:38:01,291 --> 01:38:03,041
You mean...?

1352
01:38:05,875 --> 01:38:07,333
Mom!

1353
01:38:07,416 --> 01:38:09,125
Sak got a job at the bank!

1354
01:38:09,208 --> 01:38:12,625
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

1355
01:38:14,000 --> 01:38:14,833
Great job, my son!

1356
01:38:18,916 --> 01:38:20,208
What are you doing?

1357
01:38:20,750 --> 01:38:22,416
I'm going to bed.

1358
01:38:22,875 --> 01:38:25,125
What time do you go to work on Monday?

1359
01:38:25,625 --> 01:38:26,958
Why do you ask?

1360
01:38:27,375 --> 01:38:29,583
I have something to tell you.

1361
01:38:30,250 --> 01:38:31,166
About what?

1362
01:38:31,916 --> 01:38:35,208
I will tell you when we meet. Good night!

1363
01:38:35,291 --> 01:38:36,125
What?

1364
01:39:15,250 --> 01:39:16,583
Initially,

1365
01:39:16,666 --> 01:39:19,041
I want you to work at the front.

1366
01:39:19,458 --> 01:39:21,708
-Yes, ma'am.
-If the customers have any problems,

1367
01:39:21,791 --> 01:39:23,958
or need some advice,
you can ask your senior colleagues.

1368
01:39:24,041 --> 01:39:26,125
Okay.

1369
01:39:33,916 --> 01:39:37,666
He was fired
because he messed around with a trainee.

1370
01:39:37,791 --> 01:39:40,708
It's against our rules.
Don't make the same mistake.

1371
01:39:40,791 --> 01:39:41,666
Yes, ma'am.

1372
01:39:41,750 --> 01:39:43,208
Let's continue.

1373
01:39:44,791 --> 01:39:46,541
As for this spot,

1374
01:39:46,625 --> 01:39:49,333
it's only opened
when we have too many customers.

1375
01:39:49,416 --> 01:39:50,625
MISS JARUNEE KITMANGMEE

1376
01:39:50,708 --> 01:39:52,875
Here's your desk.

1377
01:39:56,250 --> 01:40:00,000
She was our employee.

1378
01:40:00,541 --> 01:40:02,375
She just resigned.

1379
01:40:02,458 --> 01:40:04,583
But some of her stuff is still here.

1380
01:40:04,666 --> 01:40:06,958
-She quit?
-Yes.

1381
01:40:10,458 --> 01:40:11,625
Well, that's it.

1382
01:40:11,708 --> 01:40:13,833
I'll see you tomorrow.

1383
01:40:13,916 --> 01:40:15,208
Yes, ma'am.

1384
01:40:16,208 --> 01:40:20,666
Uye, can you check
if Mr. Ong-Art is coming?

1385
01:40:26,000 --> 01:40:26,916
Where are you?

1386
01:40:59,250 --> 01:41:01,333
What did you do?

1387
01:41:01,416 --> 01:41:03,083
What did I do?

1388
01:41:03,166 --> 01:41:05,708
You quit the job,
so there's an open position for me.

1389
01:41:06,000 --> 01:41:09,625
If you wanted to help me,
you didn't have to do it this way.

1390
01:41:10,083 --> 01:41:12,208
Who said I helped you?

1391
01:41:13,208 --> 01:41:14,875
So why did you quit?

1392
01:41:15,625 --> 01:41:17,625
I want to get out of my safe zone.

1393
01:41:19,583 --> 01:41:20,791
You mean...

1394
01:41:22,791 --> 01:41:23,958
you are a pilot now?

1395
01:41:26,083 --> 01:41:26,916
No.

1396
01:41:27,000 --> 01:41:28,083
What?

1397
01:41:28,708 --> 01:41:31,958
Then why are you wearing this uniform?

1398
01:41:32,041 --> 01:41:36,416
You also wore a bank uniform
when you were not an employee.

1399
01:41:37,166 --> 01:41:39,625
I want to try it, too.

1400
01:41:40,541 --> 01:41:41,791
But soon,

1401
01:41:42,708 --> 01:41:44,958
I will make it a reality...

1402
01:41:48,625 --> 01:41:49,708
like you did.

1403
01:42:03,083 --> 01:42:04,666
Are you done trying on the uniform?

1404
01:42:04,833 --> 01:42:05,916
I'm done.

1405
01:42:11,958 --> 01:42:13,958
Do you want to have dinner? My treat.

1406
01:42:14,041 --> 01:42:15,000
Sure.

1407
01:42:15,250 --> 01:42:16,833
Did you answer too quickly?

1408
01:42:16,916 --> 01:42:19,583
You don't have to treat me. We can share.

1409
01:42:20,708 --> 01:42:22,666
I'll treat you. Don't worry.

1410
01:42:23,375 --> 01:42:24,833
What a sugar daddy!

1411
01:42:25,208 --> 01:42:27,166
It's nice to eat out with a lady.

1412
01:42:29,541 --> 01:42:30,958
Can you please be my baby?

1413
01:42:39,041 --> 01:42:41,250
-I want to have pork barbeque.
-What?

1414
01:42:43,000 --> 01:42:44,833
No answer for me?

1415
01:42:45,500 --> 01:42:47,041
Let's eat first.

1416
01:42:47,125 --> 01:42:48,291
Okay?

1417
01:45:15,041 --> 01:45:17,250
Subtitle translation by
Tongta Suthummarangsi

